 Now if 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 were to transform as a tensor, then 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 will be zero at that point in all frames because tensor transformations
 only involve multiplicative factors.
 One can repeat this argument for each point thereby establishing that 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 must be zero.
 This establishes the result under the assumption stated which we now prove.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
To make 
\begin_inset Formula $K'_{ijk}=0$
\end_inset

